---

## Takeaway

The key idea is to perform a normal **Level Order BFS** while alternating the insertion direction at every level. A boolean flag determines whether to insert values at the **front** or the **back** of the current level list. This simple modification transforms a standard level order traversal into a zigzag traversal while maintaining an efficient **O(n)** time complexity.
